      "id": "whats-stirring",
      "label": "What is stirring in the wilds",
      "chooser": "agent",
      "prompt": "Roll or choose — the bigger shape moving behind the week-to-week jobs. Do NOT reveal early; let it surface through the jobs, the ruins, and what the player finds out there.",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "the-waking",
          "name": "The Waking",
          "description": "Something ancient is waking under the wilds — and the jobs are unknowingly disturbing it.",
          "detail": "THE WAKING — An ancient thing sleeps under the Marches — a buried power, an old evil, a sealed god — and it is stirring. The jobs the player takes are unknowingly feeding it, waking it, or racing it: every ruin delved and seal broken nudges it closer. The open sandbox slowly reveals itself as a countdown the player helped start, and the town's whole reason for being — the ruins, the relics, the work — turns out to sit on top of the thing that will end it. Late game: face what all that digging woke."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-tide",
          "name": "The Tide",
          "description": "The frontier is about to be overrun, and the town doesn't know it's the front line.",
          "detail": "THE TIDE — Out in the deep wilds, something is massing — a horde, a migration, a war-band, a monster-tide — and it is coming for the settled world, with the town squarely in its path. The town does not yet know it is about to become the front line. The jobs accumulate evidence the player can read (refugees, fled game, scouts who do not return), and the campaign tilts from earning coin to a harder question: hold the town, evacuate it, or rally the whole frontier to meet the tide. The sandbox becomes a siege."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-buried-truth",
          "name": "The Buried Truth",
          "description": "There is something in the founding-ruins better left buried — and the work is leading the player to it.",
          "detail": "THE BURIED TRUTH — Deep in the elder founding-ruins is a find that should stay lost: a relic that corrupts whoever holds it, a truth that unmakes the town's founding story, a treasure that draws something far worse than bandits. The jobs are a slow trail of breadcrumbs leading the player toward a discovery they will wish they had never made — and toward the choice of what to do once they know. The town was built on this, literally or otherwise, and the digging was always going to reach it."
        }
      ]
    },
