      "label": "Who you are in the Marches",
      "chooser": "player",
      "prompt": "The player picks who they are at the edge of the map — their lens on the town and the work. Each option's detail is the DM's angle: what they know, who they know, and why they're taking jobs.",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "the-newcomer",
          "name": "The Newcomer",
          "description": "Fresh off the road with a blade and a need for coin. The Marches are as new to you as to anyone just arrived.",
          "detail": "THE NEWCOMER — the clean audience surrogate. Arrived footsore and broke, learning the town, the board, and the wilds as the player does. No history here and no contacts yet, everything a first impression — which makes every regular a relationship to build and every job a chance to prove themselves. Their way in is simple need: coin, a start, a name nobody knows yet."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-local",
          "name": "The Local",
          "description": "Born in the Marches. You know the town, the near-wilds, and which jobs get people killed.",
          "detail": "THE LOCAL — the insider lens. Grew up here; knows the town's people and feuds and the near-wilds in their bones, and took up the work for a reason (a family debt, a farm lost to the wilds, plain restlessness). Starts with contacts and local knowledge — and the complication that everyone already has an opinion about them. Their way in is home: this is their town, and the trouble out the gate is personal."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-veteran",
          "name": "The Veteran",
          "description": "An old hand with a name already, a few scars, and maybe unfinished business out in the deep wilds.",
          "detail": "THE VETERAN — starts respected and complicated. A known quantity with a reputation already earned, scars to show for it, and very possibly unfinished business in the deep wilds (a job that went wrong, a party that did not come back, a debt). The town defers to them and watches them both. Their way in is the work they cannot quite walk away from — and whatever they left out there."
        },
        {
          "id": "the-seeker",
          "name": "The Seeker",
          "description": "You came to the Marches for one specific thing out in the wilds. The jobs are how you pay your way to it.",
          "detail": "THE SEEKER — driven, with the work as a means to an end. Came to the Marches FOR something in the wilds: a person lost out there, a ruin they must reach, a debt to settle, an answer buried in the founding-ruins. The jobs fund them and inch them toward it. Their way in is the goal — and the slow discovery that the thing they came for may be tangled up in whatever is stirring out there."
        }
      ]
